(firstQuint)Incidence of Delirium in Hip Fracture Patients Randomized to Regular Hypnotics vs Placebo.

 Delirium is prevalent after hip fracture surgery.

 Delirium has been linked to postoperative sleep disturbances.

 Zolpidem is a non-benzodiazepine hypnotic that preserves REM sleep.

 The present study investigates the incidence of delirium in hip fracture patients randomized to Zolpidem treatment 5 mg vs placebo in the perioperative phase.

